title: Ajax: Rebel Initiate/Ajax: Anarchist Extreme
text:
[interrupt] → When you are flatlined on your turn, flip this identity instead of losing the game. The Corp trashes the top X cards of R&D. X is equal to the amount of damage you have suffered this turn.

Flip side:
Ajax: Anarchist Extreme
Identity: Inhuman

Your maximum hand size is 0. This cannot be modified.
[interrupt] → If you would be flatlined on your turn, you may trash the top card of your stack and lose any remaining clicks instead of losing the game.
flavor: No rest! No peace!Flip side:WHATEVER THE COST!

title: Ashes of an Empire
text:
You may play this event from your heap.
After you resolve this event, end your action phase.
Make a run. When that run ends, forfeit each agenda stolen during the run and trash the top X cards of R&D where X is equal to the number of agenda points forfeited this way. If any agendas are forfeited this way the Corp must forfeit their next turn.
Remove this event from the game.

title: Ran Somewhere ATK
text:
When you install this program place 5 virus counters on it.
Instead of breaching a remote server, if this program is not already hosted in a server, you may host this program in the root of the attacked server.
All Corp cards in the root of a server hosting this program lose all abilities.
The Corp cannot install, rez, score, trash, or advance its cards in or protecting a server hosting this.
0[credit]: Purge virus counters. The Corp loses 1[credit] for each virus counter removed. Trash this program. Only the Corp can use this ability and only while this is hosted in a server.

title: Rogue Network
text:
Limit 1 hosted tag.
Whenever you take a tag, you may host it on this resource. (The tag is not considered active.)
You may remove hosted tags as if they were yours.
The Corp may trash this resource with the basic action while it is hosting a tag.
[trash], hosted tag: Take 1 tag. Choose 1 installed Corp card. Until your next turn begins, it costs 1[credit] more to rez for each tag you have at that time.

title: Dave: Demolitions Expert/Dave: New Angeles Most Wanted
text:
When your turn ends, if you've made a successful run on HQ, R&D, and Archives this turn, flip this identity and trash all installed Corp and Runner cards.

Flip side:
Dave: New Angeles Most Wanted
Identity: Felon

...the harder they fall"
flavor: "The bigger they are...Flip side:...the harder they fall"
stripped_title: Dave: Demolitions Expert/Dave: New Angeles Most Wanted

title: Gear Shift
text:
Play only as your first click.
Set aside all the cards in your grip facedown.
Draw 4 cards.
When your discard phase ends, shuffle your grip into your stack and add the cards set aside with this event back to your grip.

title: Turtles
text:
+1[mu]
Whenever you make a successful run, you may either host a copy of Turtles from your grip faceup on this Hardware or add a hosted faceup copy of Turtles to the bottom of your stack to draw 2 cards.
Limit 1 console per player
Limit 6 per deck.

title: Light the Way
text:
When your turn begins, you may choose a server.
The first time a run ends on the chosen server, you may initiate a new run on that server ignoring any additional costs.

title: Katelin: Perfected Design
text:
Your maximum hand size is equal to your unused MU.
Effects that would increase, or decrease your maximum hand size affect your memory limit instead.
You may have 1 additional console.

title: Efficiency Chip
text:
[interrupt] → While you are searching your stack for a program, you may reveal this from your stack and add it to your grip. Use the ability of only one copy of Efficiency Chip in this way per turn.
Install Efficiency Chip on a program. Lower that program's MU cost by 1. (Minimum 0.)

title: Power Relay
text: The first time you charge 1 of your installed cards each turn, you may charge another of your installed cards that hasn’t been charged this turn. (Add 1 power counter to a card that already has one.)

title: Bloodhound
text:
When you install this program and when your turn begins, you may name a card. This program can only interface with ice matching the name you last chose this way.
Interface → 1[credit]: Break 1 subroutine.
1[credit]: +2 strength.

title: Fetch
text:
When constructing your deck, choose any number of differently named cards to be part of your Stash. The cards in your Stash count towards your influence costs and limits per deck, but not your deck size. Your influence limit is additionally lowered by 1 per card in your Stash.
Before drawing your starting hand, set aside your Stash facedown. (In view of both players.)
Add a card from your Stash to your Grip.
flavor: "I can find just about anything in there." - Nova

title: Ali-ción Labs: Efficiency’s Finest
text: [click], [click], [click]: Play 1 non-terminal operation from HQ. Instead of trashing or removing it from the game, you may replay it once by paying its cost. Ignore any additional [click] costs while resolving this ability.

title: Brasília Defense System
text:
When you rez this ice during a run on this server, you may pay 1[credit] to trash one installed non-icebreaker Runner card with a [trash] ability.
When the Runner approaches this ice you may rerez it. (Derez and then rez this piece of ice, paying all costs.)
[subroutine] End the run unless the Runner trashes 1 of their installed cards.

title: Muriel 3.0
text:
Lose [click], [click], [click]: Break up to 3 subroutines on this ice. Only the Runner can use this ability.
[subroutine] The Corp gets +1 allotted [click] for their next turn.
[subroutine] Gain 1[credit].
[subroutine] You may draw one card, and/or shuffle one card from Archives or HQ into R&D.
[subroutine] End the run.

title: Corporate Efficiency Zone
text:
When your turn begins you may choose another card in the root of this server to resolve its beginning of turn triggers an additional time.
Limit 1 region per server.

title: Takamanohara: Shaping Reality
text:
You draw a starting hand of 4 cards.
Before taking your first turn, search R&D for 2 cards and add them to HQ. Shuffle 1 card from HQ into R&D.

title: Nope
text: Threat 3 → You can score this agenda during any paid ability window. (Including on the runner’s turn.)

title: Blattodea Genomics
text:
You can advance this asset.
The trash cost of each card is increased by 1 for each hosted advancement counter.

title: Coercion
text:
Play only if the Runner has at least 2 tags.
After you resolve this operation, your action phase ends.
Choose a server. The first [click] the Runner spends on their next turn must be spent to take the basic action to run that server. They cannot jack out during that run.

title: NBN: Curated Content
text:
You can look at the top card of R&D at any time.
1[credit]: Swap the top 2 cards of R&D.
3[credit]: Draw 1 card. Use this ability only once per turn.

title: Project Astro
text:
When you score this agenda, place 1 agenda counter on it for each hosted advancement counter past 3.
Hosted agenda counter: Place 1 advancement counter on an installed card.

title: Superposition
text: [interrupt] → When you would score this agenda, you may search R&D for 1 agenda with an advancement requirement equal to or less than 4. If you do, score that agenda instead and shuffle this agenda into R&D.

title: Investment Fund
text: When your turn begins, you may remove this asset from the game. If you do, shuffle 2 copies of Dividends into R&D, gain 1[credit], and draw 2 cards.

title: Dividends
text:
Gain 2[credit], [click], and draw 1 card.
Remove this operation from the game.
Cannot be included within deck building.

title: Weyland Consortium: Building the Bedrock
text: You start the game with 3 differently named kernel cards installed. (They begin unrezzed.)

title: Archives Kernel
text:
Install only protecting Archives.
Remove this ice from the game: Shuffle up to 2 cards from Archives into R&D.
[subroutine] You may choose one card in Archives to add to HQ or shuffle into R&D.
Cannot be included within deck building.

title: HQ Kernel
text:
Install only protecting R&D.
When the Runner encounters this ice, you may look at the top card of R&D.
[trash]: Shuffle R&D.
[subroutine] You may draw one card.
Cannot be included within deck building.

title: R&D Kernel
text:
Install only protecting HQ.
[trash]: The Runner may spend [click], otherwise the run cannot be declared successful. Use this ability only during a run on this server.
[subroutine] Gain 1[credit]. End the run.
Cannot be included within deck building.

title: Public Intimidation
text:
The first time you take a bad publicity each turn, do 2 meat damage if this server is not protected by ice.
When the runner trashes this asset from anywhere, they must suffer 2 meat damage, unless they remove a bad publicity.

title: Corporate Loan
text:
Gain 6[credit].
When your turn begins, if this card is faceup in Archives, remove it from the game and lose 3[credit].

title: Subdivision
text:
Install only in the root of HQ.
When you rez this upgrade choose another identity from the same faction and host it on this upgrade. Remove hosted identity from the game when this upgrade is uninstalled, or derezed.
Hosted identity text is active.
When the runner would breach HQ, they may instead access this upgrade. If they choose not to, they cannot access this upgrade during the breach.
Limit 1 per deck.

title: Change in Leadership
text:
[interrupt] → When you would mulligan, you may reveal this operation from HQ and set it aside. If you do, draw 1 fewer card for the mulligan, then return this operation to HQ.
Draw 2 cards. Shuffle 2 cards from HQ into R&D. Gain [click].
flavor: I promise I can turn this ship around, or I'll throw myself overboard.

title: 40YCR Chip
text: [trash]: Run any server. The Corp may pay 5[credit] to prevent this. Use this ability only in the paid ability window immediately after someone finishes taking an action.
flavor: "One mine of many." - New Angeles Most Wanted
